                     <part>Tsingtauer Neueste Nachrichten</part>
                  </title>, 1910", "<title>
                     <part>Memorandum on the Political Situation</part>
                  </title> typescript by Edward Selby Little, 1910", and "Typescript translation of the <title>
                     <part>Official Gazette</part>
                  </title> by Dr. Tenney [?], March 15, 1909". Three documents were rehoused in "Invoices and accounts, circa 1907-1911": Viney's <title>
                     <part>Security for Overdrafts at the Russo-Chinese (Asiatic) Bank</part>
                  </title> and two invoices for Viney's payments to his Chinese language teacher.</p>
